In a Spring Boot application, the code is usually organized into a few key files and packages. 
Here's a breakdown of the main code files you'll typically find (or write):

src/
 └── main/
     ├── java/
     │    └── com/example/demo/
     │         ├── DemoApplication.java       ← 🟢 Main class (entry point)
     │         ├── controller/
     │         │     └── HelloController.java ← 🌐 API endpoints
     │         ├── service/
     │         │     └── HelloService.java    ← 🧠 Business logic
     │         ├── repository/
     │         │     └── UserRepository.java  ← 💾 Database access
     │         └── model/
     │               └── User.java            ← 📦 Domain model/entity
     └── resources/
          ├── application.properties         ← ⚙️ App configuration
          ├── static/                        ← 🌐 Static files (HTML, CSS, JS)
          └── templates/                     ← 🖼️ Thymeleaf or other view templates
